<div id="review_2504698223" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2504698223" />
    <a title="Mike Burrell" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/2598515-mike-burrell"><img alt="Mike Burrell" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1525709128p2/2598515.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2504698223?book_show_action=true">Aug 24, 2018</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Mike Burrell" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Mike Burrell" href="/user/show/2598515-mike-burrell">Mike Burrell</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2504698223" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer12901671727899517345">Author Steve McCondichie’s protagonist, Jesse Few, is a 21st Century Willy Loman. He finds himself growing well into middle-age with nothing to show but a string of girlfriends, his aging golfing buddies, and a career as a hustling marketing manager that he now finds unfulfilling. Life is coming up fast on Jesse. His mother is sinking into senility, suffering hallucinations of some deep secret from the past. He suddenly realizes his ex wife was the love of his life, and his two children have gro</span>
  <span id="freeText12901671727899517345" style="display:none">Author Steve McCondichie’s protagonist, Jesse Few, is a 21st Century Willy Loman. He finds himself growing well into middle-age with nothing to show but a string of girlfriends, his aging golfing buddies, and a career as a hustling marketing manager that he now finds unfulfilling. Life is coming up fast on Jesse. His mother is sinking into senility, suffering hallucinations of some deep secret from the past. He suddenly realizes his ex wife was the love of his life, and his two children have grown to teenagers with him as a sometimes weekend dad. If those aren’t enough problems and regrets, his son gets arrested for DUI and drug possession in the company of the under-age daughter of an unscrupulous biker preacher. And there’s the little matter of looming financial ruin, stemming from an improvident real estate investment. Jesse has always been able to talk (sometimes lie) his way through his problems, but will his silver tongue get him over this tsunami of a middle-age crisis? <br /><br />Though written in a fast moving, humorous prose, set in the south and cast with a wild assortment of southern characters, the story could have happened anywhere. We’ve all seen some Jesse Fews. Those guys who at one time had been too young, too horny, too ambitious, and in too much of a hurry to see the real thing passing them by. We may not like Jesse at first, but we can see the potential behind the BS and hope he salvages something from the wreckage. <br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="12901671727899517345" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


